00:46.681 --> 00:48.241
<i>Dirk Kowalski on set, please!</i>

00:48.601 --> 00:52.241
1000 MEXICANS

00:52.481 --> 00:54.881
<i>Quiet please, we're ready to shoot!</i>

00:57.641 --> 00:59.481
<i>Where are the sweeties?</i>

01:03.321 --> 01:05.361
You're on a diet!

01:07.881 --> 01:09.121
Hi, pal!

01:11.801 --> 01:14.561
I can't wear those, Jenny.
I attract women.

01:16.201 --> 01:17.921
<i>Has anyone seen Dirk?</i>

01:19.961 --> 01:21.001
Watch out!

01:21.721 --> 01:25.401
Out of my way or you'll get a chop!
The karate kind, not pork!

01:25.841 --> 01:28.601
You could do with a few bitch slaps!

01:28.841 --> 01:31.801
Show a bit more respect, Boris,
if you ever want to work for me.

01:32.041 --> 01:34.121
Dream on, Adamsky!

01:35.161 --> 01:37.641
Move the motorhome.
It's in our way.

01:37.881 --> 01:40.441
Aye, aye, Captain!
- Great, acid drops!

01:59.961 --> 02:02.441
Man!
What the hell's going on here?

02:03.001 --> 02:05.321
I can't get a moment's peace!

02:05.721 --> 02:08.321
All this stress here
will kill me one day!

02:08.881 --> 02:10.481
Dirk! Relax!

02:11.681 --> 02:13.601
I need your autograph.

02:13.841 --> 02:16.401
My buddy's a huge fan of yours.

02:18.281 --> 02:21.041
You see, Lukas,
for me they always come first:

02:21.281 --> 02:24.241
the little sheep
who diligently work here

02:24.601 --> 02:27.201
and occasionally squeeze out
a few droppings.

02:27.761 --> 02:31.361
Do you understand?
I'm not a wolf. I'm a kind of sheepdog.

02:31.601 --> 02:34.361
I protect the herd.
I keep them together.

02:34.921 --> 02:37.201
Thierry,
what are you talking about?

02:37.601 --> 02:40.681
I thought I'd start
with a snappy metaphor,

02:41.041 --> 02:42.961
but let's get down to brass tacks.

02:44.441 --> 02:46.281
When we're finished,

02:46.801 --> 02:50.361
I'm making you Senior
Creative Art Director.

02:50.841 --> 02:53.161
You'll be boss!
How about that?

02:59.561 --> 03:01.561
Wow! That's really...

03:03.201 --> 03:05.921
You're as useful
as a shit-flavored lollipop.

03:06.761 --> 03:11.161
Sorry, Wolfgang, the van was in my blind
spot... We'll come to that later.

03:11.521 --> 03:14.281
You can't just go
and ask Dirk Kowalski

03:14.641 --> 03:15.801
for his autograph.

03:16.121 --> 03:19.841
Stalkers with homemade fan buttons do that,
but not team members.

03:21.041 --> 03:23.361
We can't find Dirk
and we're ready to shoot.

03:24.361 --> 03:27.041
Then do the reverse shots first.

03:27.401 --> 03:30.721
And hire a five-star motorhome for Dirk.
That'll relax him.

03:31.081 --> 03:32.241
You got it!

03:32.481 --> 03:34.281
"You got it!"

03:34.521 --> 03:36.481
It's your fault, dickwad!

03:36.761 --> 03:38.601
Get your stuff and go!

03:43.401 --> 03:44.401
Know what?

03:44.721 --> 03:46.081
This was worth it.

03:46.321 --> 03:48.961
Your firm's as lousy
as your broken executive chair!

03:49.721 --> 03:51.601
Anyway, you can't fire me.
- Yeah?

03:52.041 --> 03:54.401
"Yeah?". I quit!

03:54.641 --> 03:57.321
Great!
I don't have to give you severance pay.

03:57.561 --> 03:59.841
Huh?
- I'll give you a nice reference.

04:00.241 --> 04:03.761
If you don't get the 8,000 euros
you owe me for the van

04:04.001 --> 04:06.761
and put it on my desk
by next week,

04:07.121 --> 04:11.561
I'll see to it that you never work
in the film industry again.

04:12.881 --> 04:14.201
8,000 euros?

04:15.801 --> 04:18.281
I didn't mean to...
- Get out!

04:29.201 --> 04:31.361
I'd like you to imagine this:

04:31.601 --> 04:34.241
you're sitting with your dream woman

04:35.361 --> 04:37.601
in a beautiful field of flowers.

04:38.281 --> 04:41.041
The last rays of sunlight
are turning the sky

04:42.321 --> 04:44.641
into bronze-colored honey.

04:45.481 --> 04:47.921
Bronze-colored honey?
- Yes.

04:48.601 --> 04:50.521
What's wrong with it?
- Sounds shit.

04:52.041 --> 04:53.881
Golden honey sounds better.

04:57.361 --> 04:59.081
I've been thinking.

04:59.321 --> 05:01.641
Let's start our own production firm,

05:02.001 --> 05:05.601
like we were going to.
"Mad Eagle" was just the beginning, dude!

05:05.841 --> 05:09.401
Not that again.
- Why the Jean Claude Van Damme not?

05:09.641 --> 05:13.161
The important thing is:
you deal with the creative shit and I...

05:13.641 --> 05:15.081
do everything else.

05:15.441 --> 05:17.641
Including the casting couch again.

05:18.121 --> 05:20.801
You didn't raise one cent,
Mr. Producer.

05:21.041 --> 05:24.481
I was on the verge of
securing a major deal!

05:25.921 --> 05:29.841
If you hadn't started at the agency,
we'd be raking it in now.

05:30.681 --> 05:32.601
Oh, they've fired you.

05:33.321 --> 05:35.521
That's why you're going on
about that again.

05:36.561 --> 05:39.121
Plus, you've bought alcohol-free beer.

05:47.801 --> 05:50.481
Then let's go
for a real afterwork drink.

05:50.721 --> 05:53.921
No way! I've got to be
fit for work tomorrow.

05:54.641 --> 05:56.321
I'm in shock from being fired.

05:56.561 --> 05:58.881
I bought alcohol-free beer.

06:03.401 --> 06:05.601
One shot, here at home!

06:11.521 --> 06:14.721
Grandpa, gimme another! Please!

06:15.201 --> 06:18.801
You and your pal should go home.
You've had enough.

06:19.161 --> 06:21.321
I decide when I've had enough.

06:21.681 --> 06:23.361
Yeah, but not here.

06:23.601 --> 06:26.641
My joint, my rules.
- But he's asleep, too.

06:28.641 --> 06:31.241
That's Rainer the Eel: furniture.
Scram!

06:32.921 --> 06:34.721
And if I don't?

06:35.841 --> 06:38.401
I'll teach you to fly without wings.

06:49.561 --> 06:52.961
Another tray of Mexicans, please.
- There's none left.

06:53.401 --> 06:55.521
But for you, I'll mix some more.

07:38.921 --> 07:40.801
A beer and a Mexican, Earl.

07:41.161 --> 07:42.801
Hey, you lovely ladies!

07:43.601 --> 07:46.201
Objection!
- Sustained! - Hi, Martin.

07:46.561 --> 07:48.681
Dude!
- Everything OK?

07:48.921 --> 07:52.281
You scared the hell out of me.
- So how's it going?

07:53.081 --> 07:54.561
Yeah...
- Yeah?

07:54.961 --> 07:56.321
It's going...

07:57.121 --> 07:58.761
down the pan.

07:59.401 --> 08:02.481
Mila's dreamed of this wedding
since she was about 12.

08:03.241 --> 08:06.241
It has to be perfect.
There's so much to remember.

08:07.001 --> 08:10.681
The right priest,
a de-escalation-oriented seating plan.

08:11.721 --> 08:15.561
One of Mila's aunts only eats stuff
that falls from trees.

08:16.161 --> 08:19.801
Does that mean I have to throw
the suckling pig from a tree?

08:21.961 --> 08:23.281
I can do the discofox.

08:23.961 --> 08:26.481
It's one of seven dances
I have to learn by Sunday.

08:26.721 --> 08:28.441
Shit, you're totally fucked.

08:29.561 --> 08:32.361
I love Mila.
You know that, don't you?

08:33.520 --> 08:34.881
Sure. Why?

08:35.961 --> 08:38.280
I've screwed up.
- What did you do?

08:38.841 --> 08:42.361
The movie team backed out.
It was the only thing I had to organize.

08:43.081 --> 08:46.961
We wanted to have the whole wedding
filmed by professionals.

08:49.041 --> 08:52.161
How about another drink for you ladies?

08:53.481 --> 08:56.761
You guys made that "Mad Eagle" film.
- Yeah.

08:57.481 --> 08:59.281
Couldn't you film our wedding?

08:59.641 --> 09:01.641
You're wedding filmmakers?

09:02.001 --> 09:04.161
How romantic is that?

09:04.561 --> 09:06.441
Yeah, that's right.

09:06.961 --> 09:09.121
I was just about to tell you.

09:09.361 --> 09:11.721
Wedding film makers are in demand.

09:12.481 --> 09:17.121
Right. It's peak season,
all the teams are booked. I'd pay you.

09:23.881 --> 09:24.881
We'll do it.

09:25.201 --> 09:27.201
We can't let a friend down.

09:27.441 --> 09:28.881
Can we, Lukas?

09:29.241 --> 09:31.241
We'll do it:
the whole enchilada.

09:31.721 --> 09:33.721
From wedding vows
to wedding night.

09:34.641 --> 09:36.361
The wedding night?

09:36.601 --> 09:39.001
You mean it?
You really mean it?

09:39.641 --> 09:41.121
I won't forget this!

09:41.481 --> 09:44.041
Another round of Mexicans, ladies?

09:47.441 --> 09:49.481
Wow, awesome!
1,000 Mexicans!

09:51.121 --> 09:53.321
Mexicans all round!

10:02.321 --> 10:05.441
Another tray!
That was just the beginning!

10:47.921 --> 10:48.921
Secure.

10:56.521 --> 10:58.761
Fuck me sideways! Fromsbert.

11:01.161 --> 11:03.921
That was a long time ago, Adam.
My name's Rocko now.

11:04.281 --> 11:06.881
Yeah, right.
Fromsbert, Martin's brother.

11:07.281 --> 11:08.881
What happened to you?

11:09.121 --> 11:11.881
He was such a skinny little shit!

11:12.241 --> 11:15.801
I work as a government bodyguard
in high-risk areas:

11:16.041 --> 11:18.361
Afghanistan, Libya, Iraq.

11:20.601 --> 11:22.721
That's a souvenir from Yemen.

11:23.641 --> 11:28.041
Today at 03:00 Bravo time you made a
promise to my brother Martin. Sit.

11:29.601 --> 11:30.641
Sit.

11:34.801 --> 11:37.961
The top brass
have asked me to be best man.

11:38.401 --> 11:42.561
So I'm responsible for the accompanying
areas of responsibility. One of which...

11:43.761 --> 11:45.641
is the wedding movie.

11:46.161 --> 11:48.241
It was just a ploy.
- Really?

11:48.801 --> 11:51.241
What did you think?
- I meant it, Rocky.

11:51.601 --> 11:54.481
You shook on it,
so I'd say it's legally binding.

11:54.721 --> 12:00.321
And as Martin's been getting you two out of
legal scrapes for years, you owe it to him.

12:00.961 --> 12:04.521
Martin's relying on you
and he's posted it already.

12:05.401 --> 12:09.641
In my profession,
we call this the "point of no return."

12:14.401 --> 12:15.961
I've got to go to work.

12:20.241 --> 12:24.881
I worked for three days on what I'm about
to show you. You'd better stay and watch.

12:28.841 --> 12:32.521
Briefing: Martin is getting married
on Sunday at 10:00 Bravo time.

12:33.121 --> 12:36.761
To get everyone in the right mood,
your film will be shown beforehand.

12:37.001 --> 12:42.201
You'll find all the relevant info, such as
timing and coordinates, in this handout.

12:46.601 --> 12:49.361
Wow, our first commissioned film, Lukas.

12:50.081 --> 12:52.361
By the way:
cool presentation, Rocky.

12:52.601 --> 12:54.281
Thanks. Fridge?

12:58.201 --> 13:03.201
If this operation fails, I'll be wearing
the brown helmet, so it's not an option.

13:04.401 --> 13:06.041
Low-fat.

13:06.401 --> 13:07.761
Perfect.

13:08.761 --> 13:10.601
The whole works, huh?

13:11.121 --> 13:12.201
Well...

13:12.441 --> 13:13.721
Have fun.

13:27.641 --> 13:30.401
I'd like you to imagine this:

13:31.881 --> 13:35.361
you're sitting with a woman
in a lovely field of flowers.

13:37.201 --> 13:39.961
You look deep into each other's eyes.

13:41.361 --> 13:45.321
The last suns contaminate the sky
with bronze-colored...

13:45.681 --> 13:47.041
With golden honey.

13:50.241 --> 13:53.201
Busy as ever.
Very authentic. I like!

13:53.841 --> 13:55.521
Can I steal you for a sec?

13:55.881 --> 13:58.201
We're right in the middle.
- No problem.

13:58.561 --> 14:01.201
Maurice is totally in the picture.

14:01.441 --> 14:03.001
Come on.

14:06.361 --> 14:07.481
Hi.

14:09.321 --> 14:11.321
What was that all about?

14:13.481 --> 14:16.921
A truly excellent Cohiba, Thierry.
- You said it.

14:19.561 --> 14:23.001
We know each other from the sauna.
- It's a small world.

14:23.241 --> 14:24.641
By the way.

14:25.001 --> 14:26.961
Rocko has kindly drawn my attention

14:27.201 --> 14:30.041
to the immense emotional pressure
you're under.

14:30.401 --> 14:33.361
And I have to admit,
it hadn't escaped me.

14:34.321 --> 14:37.601
You're pale, you're shaking
and the dog doesn't like you.

14:38.281 --> 14:40.864
We think a short vacation
would do you good.

14:40.889 --> 14:43.585
After all, you'll soon
be a sheepdog, like me.

14:43.801 --> 14:47.321
I can't use an emotional wreck.
- But the Schätzing campaign was my idea.

14:48.241 --> 14:51.841
The layout for the photo shoot,
the website: all mine.

14:52.441 --> 14:56.161
Maurice will take over.
He's learned from the best: you.

14:57.241 --> 14:59.481
His name is Moritz.
He isn't Maurice.

15:00.401 --> 15:02.961
Am I off the campaign now?
- Listen.

15:03.401 --> 15:07.481
When one door closes,
another one opens somewhere else.

15:08.041 --> 15:10.681
Anyway, you're lucky
to have a friend like Rocko.

15:10.921 --> 15:13.361
They're few and far between.

15:14.121 --> 15:16.961
What a cute little fellow.
- Isn't he just?

15:22.201 --> 15:23.521
Shit!

15:35.921 --> 15:37.841
That's sweet of you.
Are they for me?

15:38.241 --> 15:41.721
Thanks to you and Rocko they laid me off.
Know what that means?

15:42.761 --> 15:45.121
That we can help
our frantic friend Martin.

15:47.241 --> 15:49.201
I can't do it without you, Lukas.

15:50.281 --> 15:51.681
I have something for you.

15:55.681 --> 15:57.401
Dirk Kowalski's autograph.

16:00.241 --> 16:01.521
That's it?

16:02.121 --> 16:05.201
You pester me for weeks
and now you're not pleased?

16:06.961 --> 16:09.321
What's he like in person?
- Totally cool.

16:10.361 --> 16:14.681
Where'd you get the wheels?
- The guy from the motorhome hire owed me.

16:15.281 --> 16:17.641
Come on,
I want to show you something.

16:23.721 --> 16:27.241
Air conditioning, hands-free speakerphone,
DVB-T tuner,

16:27.481 --> 16:30.601
kitchen, toilet, shower,
and a fully equipped

16:30.961 --> 16:33.321
editing studio... Shit!

16:34.161 --> 16:35.961
This is our new production van.

16:37.841 --> 16:41.081
That's your cell. I've connected it
to the speakerphone.

16:43.041 --> 16:48.081
<i>Oh, my head! Martin speaking.
I just wanted to say I can't come today.</i>

16:48.321 --> 16:50.921
<i>Hopefully I'll be fit again
for the wedding in four days.</i>

16:51.161 --> 16:54.561
<i>I don't want Mila to leave me
standing at the altar like her ex.</i>

16:54.801 --> 16:58.161
I'm counting on you <i>guys.</i>
- Relax, everything's under control.

16:58.561 --> 17:02.201
We're interviewing the parents in
30 minutes. Over and out. Right.

17:02.441 --> 17:05.721
OK, I'll drive.
- Fine. I'll do our homework.

17:10.080 --> 17:12.481
I've made us a really awesome mix tape.

17:56.921 --> 17:59.041
Welcome to wedding hell!

17:59.281 --> 18:02.041
And the devil wears Pr...
- Protection vests.

18:02.401 --> 18:04.321
Put these in the boathouse.

18:05.081 --> 18:07.481
Martin isn't coming:
he's sick in bed.

18:08.081 --> 18:12.521
He can't take his drink anymore. You
should let him off the leash more often.

18:12.881 --> 18:14.281
He's a free agent.

18:14.521 --> 18:17.321
At least on Mondays, that's girls' night.
- Lucky guy!

18:17.681 --> 18:20.521
Come on,
we'll do the interviews in the lounge.

18:20.881 --> 18:23.641
It's the only free space
here at Knackstedt Castle.

18:24.281 --> 18:27.041
Just one thing...
- Who do I hear there?

18:29.641 --> 18:31.881
For God's sake...

18:34.321 --> 18:38.481
Good to see that the ravages of time
are getting to you guys as well.

18:39.321 --> 18:41.481
We're trying to age gracefully,
like you.

18:42.161 --> 18:43.761
Heinz-Dieter Knackstedt!

18:44.361 --> 18:46.681
